history.content:
MDB is hosting an infosession for Yugabyte TONIGHT (Wednesday, 11/18/20) at 6:00 PM! Yugabyte, a Series-B startup founded by ex-Berkeley alumni, is recruiting for both intern and full time software engineering positions.
Facebook Event: https://www.facebook.com/events/856828168477451
Zoom Link: https://yugabyte.zoom.us/j/83570025323?pwd=VVlOVUw1bDZleCtXNUlSQ241bE9Ndz09
Yugabyte is the company behind YugabyteDB an open-source, high-performance, distributed SQL database for powering services that require scale, geographic data distribution and resilience. In an increasingly multi/hybrid-cloud world, YugabyteDB is enabling companies across verticals such as retail, e-commerce, finance, ad-tech, IoT & cybersecurity break free from legacy/single-node databases, re-platform their data layer for scale and avoid cloud lock-in.
Yugabyte is a venture backed, Series-B stage startup founded by Kannan, Karthik, and Mikhail, ex-Facebook engineers who played a key role in building & scaling databases like Cassandra & HBase for use cases such as Facebook Messenger and Facebook's Operational Data Store during Facebook's explosive growth from 50M to 1B+ users.
We are looking for talented and driven individuals that share our passion to build a lasting and impactful company. We would love for you to consider joining Yugabyte's growing R&D team in the Bay Area (US), Toronto (Canada) or remotely.
